            [
                'id'           => 17,
                'title'        => 'E-Commerce in Southeast Asia Hits $200 Billion',
                'slug'         => 'ecommerce-southeast-asia-200-billion',
                'excerpt'      => 'The region sees unprecedented online sales growth driven by mobile commerce.',
                'content'      => "Southeast Asia's e-commerce market has crossed the \$200 billion annual transaction value milestone, according to the latest report from Google, Temasek, and Bain & Company. The achievement came a full two years ahead of projections made in 2022, driven by accelerating smartphone adoption, improving logistics networks, and a structural shift in consumer behavior following the pandemic.\n\nIndonesia remains the region's largest single e-commerce market, accounting for approximately 45% of total transaction value. Tokopedia, Shopee, and Lazada continue to dominate, but new entrants — particularly in social commerce, where products are sold directly through social media platforms — are gaining significant ground among younger consumers.\n\nThe growth of live streaming commerce has been particularly notable. Platforms combining entertainment with shopping have generated billions of dollars in transactions, with some individual content creators selling more merchandise in a single live session than traditional retailers move in a month.\n\nLogistics infrastructure, once the biggest constraint on e-commerce growth, has improved dramatically. Same-day delivery is now available in 40 Indonesian cities, and next-day delivery covers over 90% of Java and Bali. Investment in last-mile networks in Sumatra and Kalimantan is accelerating.\n\nMicrosoft and Google are competing aggressively for the cloud infrastructure contracts that underpin these platforms, recognizing Southeast Asia as one of the fastest-growing cloud markets globally. Investment in regional data center capacity is expected to exceed \$15 billion over the next three years.",
                'image_url'    => 'https://picsum.photos/seed/ecommerce/800/400',
                'category_id'  => 5,
                'author'       => 'Eko Prasetyo',
                'views'        => 8900,
                'published_at' => '2026-04-29 13:00:00',
