            [
                'id'           => 18,
                'title'        => '5G Rollout Reaches 80% of Indonesian Population',
                'slug'         => '5g-rollout-indonesia-80-percent',
                'excerpt'      => 'Ultra-fast connectivity is transforming how Indonesians work and communicate.',
                'content'      => "Indonesia's three major mobile network operators have collectively announced that 5G coverage now reaches 80% of the country's population, following an intensive 18-month infrastructure buildout that covered 50 cities and regencies across 22 provinces. The milestone makes Indonesia one of the fastest 5G deployers among emerging markets.\n\nFor most urban Indonesians, the practical impact of 5G has been immediate. Download speeds that previously averaged 40-60 Mbps on 4G now routinely exceed 400 Mbps, enabling seamless 4K video streaming, real-time cloud gaming, and near-instantaneous large file transfers.\n\nBeyond consumer applications, 5G is enabling industrial transformation. Several manufacturing facilities in Karawang and Bekasi have deployed private 5G networks to support autonomous guided vehicles, real-time quality control via machine vision, and remote operation of heavy machinery. These \"smart factory\" implementations are showing productivity gains of 15-25% in early deployments.\n\nAgriculture is another sector benefiting from connectivity improvements. In parts of Central Java, 5G-connected soil sensors and drone systems are enabling precision farming techniques that reduce water usage by 30% while increasing crop yields. The Ministry of Agriculture has launched a program to expand these pilots nationally.\n\nChallenges remain, particularly in reaching the 20% of the population — largely in rural Papua and Maluku — where 5G deployment is economically difficult. The government's Universal Service Obligation fund is being restructured to address this digital divide.",
                'image_url'    => 'https://picsum.photos/seed/5g/800/400',
